content.text:
The claim is about a hypothetical counterfactual scenario - "If California had increased per-pupil funding by 10% in 2002, at least three additional directly funded schools would have opened in Stanislaus County by the end of 2005."

This is a counterfactual/hypothetical claim about what *would have happened* under different funding conditions. The database contains historical records of what actually happened - it records which schools opened and when, and their funding types. However, it does not contain:

1. Any per-pupil funding data
2. Any causal model linking funding levels to school openings
3. Any way to predict how many additional schools would have opened under hypothetical funding increases

The database simply records facts about schools. It cannot tell us what would have happened under a different funding scenario. This is a speculative/counterfactual claim that cannot be verified or refuted with the data available.
